<paragraph blockId="49.[189,1399,405,502]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis box="[189,398,406,431]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
Nycteris 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1876" box="[296,398,406,431]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Nanonycteris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrotis">macrotis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has a scattered distribution over CRB, where it occurs in almost all regions, except for the northwestern part of the 
<collectingCountry box="[570,634,441,467]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">DRC</collectingCountry>
. The SDM map suggests a wide distribution across Africa south of the Sahara.
</paragraph>
